snippet.textDisplay: It's kind of sad when you think about it, out of the 8 years it was in development, the first 5-6 years would have been exclusively dedicated to those older consoles and PC, because they wouldn't have even had PS5/series X/S dev kits to work on programming for. So the vast majority of their time was spent preparing the game for those consoles-and they were done so badly the games couldn't even play most of the time (like the PS4 having an issue with crashing during one of the first scenes repeatedly). It's almost like the programming didn't even start until half a decade after it was announced, and they just focused on storyboards, concepts, and proposed visual designs.
snippet.textOriginal: It's kind of sad when you think about it, out of the 8 years it was in development, the first 5-6 years would have been exclusively dedicated to those older consoles and PC, because they wouldn't have even had PS5/series X/S dev kits to work on programming for. So the vast majority of their time was spent preparing the game for those consoles-and they were done so badly the games couldn't even play most of the time (like the PS4 having an issue with crashing during one of the first scenes repeatedly). It's almost like the programming didn't even start until half a decade after it was announced, and they just focused on storyboards, concepts, and proposed visual designs.
